This jump from “Gnarnia The Movie” was 85-90 miles per hour (142kph) and 311ft in distance (94.7 meters) 

This is the furthest I’ve ever gone on a dirtbike and surprisingly it felt comfortable. It felt gnarly going 85-90 miles per hour and hitting a ramp. This is after I came up short on the same ramp set up with a 150 ft gap about 6 months prior destroying myself (broken pelvis in 2 places, broken back, shoulder blade, torn groin, torn rotator cuff and labrum) requiring 4 surgeries as seen in my movie “Gnarnia”. When we reached 311ft it was after only one day of jumping and of coarse I wanted more, but as a group decision between the jump crew, my Dad, and myself we all decided to end the movie on a good note, live to jump another day, and make it to X Games 6 weeks later. I am passionate about distance jumping and I feel I excel at this type of jumping so one day I plan to revisit this jump. Id love to push it further in the dream of one day getting closer to breaking a world record.
